CHANGELOG.md:523:- Added depth-2 sw_sampler end-to-end test coverage (frac-0116): `tests/test_sw_sampler.py` now includes `SwSamplerEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing `my-claw/tools/senseweave/synthesis/sw_sampler.scd` granular SynthDef source and the SC-side runtime harness `my-claw/supercollider/test_sw_sampler.scd` through one diagnostic lifecycle. The test extracts every documented SynthDef control default (`bufnum`, `amp`, `grain_size_ms=80.0`, `density=12.0`, `position`, `position_rate`, `pitch_transpose_semitones`, `pitch_jitter_semitones`, `attack_sec`, `release_sec`, `gate>=1`, `out_bus=0`, `fx_bus`, `fx_send=0.4`), verifies the integrated granular signal-chain order (`Impulse.kr` -> `TRand.kr` -> `.midiratio` -> `Sweep.ar`/`Phasor.ar` -> `GrainBuf.ar(... bufnum ...)` -> `EnvGen.kr(Env.asr, gate, doneAction: 2)` -> dry `Out.ar(out_bus, ...)` -> parallel `Out.ar(fx_bus, ...)` send) on a comment-stripped source, confirms the dry write to `out_bus` is not scaled by `fx_send` so the parallel-send architecture is preserved, inspects the SC-side runtime harness for source compile, 2-second render, non-silence, FFT spectral peak, gate=0 release tail, and known-content buffer allocation, and round-trips a JSON-safe diagnostic of the SynthDef name, source path, runtime-harness path, defaults, signal-chain stages, stage positions, and runtime checks through `json.dumps(..., sort_keys=True)`. `tests/test_test_sw_sampler_depth.py` pins the test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the named end-to-end class/method. Existing production behavior remains unchanged because the SCD source and SC-side harness already produced the required one-path output; startup identity anchors remain green (`11 passed`) and the full validation gate (`4669 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remains clean, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
CHANGELOG.md:539:- Added depth-2 router end-to-end test coverage (frac-0108): `tests/test_router.py` now includes `RouterEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing `promptclaw/router.py` public surface through one realistic routing lifecycle. The coverage exercises `agent_catalog_markdown(...)` enabled-agent rendering, `heuristic_route(...)` lead/verifier selection on a code-implementation task with confidence above the ambiguous threshold, trust-score filtering that shifts the lead away from `codex` when trust drops to zero, ambiguity detection plus clarification-question generation on a vague prompt with reduced confidence, full `route_markdown(...)` rendering of lead/verifier/task-type/confidence/reason/handoff sections (including the conditional clarification block), JSON round-tripping through `parse_route_decision(...)` with structural equality on `lead_agent`/`verifier_agent`/`task_type`/`ambiguous`/`reason`/`subtask_brief`/`confidence`, and a JSON-safe diagnostic round trip via `json.dumps(..., sort_keys=True)`. `tests/test_test_router_depth.py` pins the router test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the named end-to-end class/method. Existing production behavior remains unchanged because the router module already produced meaningful one-path output; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4653 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
CHANGELOG.md:565:- Added depth-2 orchestral-form end-to-end test coverage (frac-0099): `tests/test_orchestral_form.py` now includes `OrchestralFormEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing `my-claw/tools/senseweave/synthesis/orchestral_form.py` public surface through one development-climax-to-resolution flow: complete tutti role grouping, diverging crescendo counts, converging diminuendo counts, effect-budget gates for tinting/sfp/tutti/new timbre, dramatic sfp pair selection, post-tutti silence, breath reentry, and JSON-safe diagnostic serialization. `tests/test_test_orchestral_form_depth.py` pins the orchestral-form test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing production behavior remains unchanged because the module already produced meaningful one-path output; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4592 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
CHANGELOG.md:569:- Added depth-2 Ollama routing end-to-end test coverage (frac-0097): `tests/test_ollama_routing.py` now includes `OllamaRoutingEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing `my-claw/tools/agent_selector.py` Ollama route surface through the default dual-socket role table, unknown-category default fallback, one merged `OLLAMA_ROUTE_JSON` override payload, ignored incomplete override data, route-copy isolation after caller mutation, and JSON-safe diagnostic serialization. `tests/test_test_ollama_routing_depth.py` pins the routing test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing production routing behavior remains unchanged because it already produced meaningful one-path output; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4588 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
CHANGELOG.md:633:- Added depth-2 coherence-engine end-to-end test coverage (frac-0065): `tests/test_coherence_engine.py` now ships a new `TestCoherenceEngineEndToEnd` class that drives the existing public `CoherenceEngine` and `NullCoherenceEngine` surface through complete end-to-end paths. The new tests walk every hook in canonical order (`pre_routing → post_routing → pre_lead → post_lead → pre_verify → post_verify → finalize`) and verify event types, phases, monotonic sequence numbers, run-id propagation, and SQLite persistence across an engine rebuild; write a `constitution.json` with one HARD and one SOFT keyword rule and confirm `EnforcementMode.FULL` blocks `post_routing`/`post_lead`/`post_verify` while `EnforcementMode.MONITOR` records the same violations without blocking, propagating HARD severity, both rule ids, and a negative trust delta on `post_lead`; record two architectural decisions through `record_decision` and confirm `pre_routing`/`pre_lead`/`pre_verify` inject the `## Active Decisions` block with at least one matching title; step the graduation manager across three `finalize` calls plus alternating `record_graduation_observation` outcomes and verify the run/observation/true-/false-positive counters and stable enforcement mode; round-trip a full replayed event payload through `json.dumps` with sorted keys and verify each event's `sequence_number`, `run_id`, and dict `payload`; and loop `NullCoherenceEngine` across multiple run ids confirming every hook returns an approved verdict with empty violations and empty injected context plus an empty replay. `tests/test_test_coherence_engine_depth.py` pins `tests/test_coherence_engine.py` at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing `TestCoherenceEngine` and `TestNullCoherenceEngine` assertions and the production `promptclaw/coherence/engine.py` source remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4421 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green.
CHANGELOG.md:639:- Added depth-2 capstone-engine end-to-end test coverage (frac-0062): `tests/test_capstone_engine.py` now includes `TestCapstoneCycleEndToEnd`, which drives the existing public `build_capstone_cycle()` API through complete EMSD capstone planning paths. The new tests verify all five canonical phases expose linked family, patch, arc, palette, mix, sampling, and DSP contracts; assert occupied Theramini routing activates the Conversation dialogue path and ducking behavior; assert away-practice late phases retarget sampling and DSP focus to `self_bus`; compare quiet cadences against occupied cycles for lower density and quieter mix targets; verify repertoire songs shape identity families, patches, imagery, and statement text; and round-trip phase diagnostics through `json.dumps`. `tests/test_capstone_engine_depth.py` pins the file's fractal depth at >= 2 (now `substantial (no tests)`, 9 real functions versus 2 trivial). Existing capstone assertions and `my-claw/tools/senseweave/capstone_engine.py` source behavior remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4401 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green.
CHANGELOG.md:645:- Added depth-2 artist-identity end-to-end test coverage (frac-0059): `tests/test_artist_identity.py` now ships a `TestArtistIdentityEndToEnd` class that drives the existing public artist-identity surface (`select_mode`, `apply_mode_to_commission`, `next_tonal_choice`, `MODES`, `MODES_BY_NAME`, `HOME_TONAL_MAP`, `VOICE_ROLES`, `SIGNATURE_VOICES`) through looped, table-driven end-to-end methods. The new tests sweep every `ArtistMode` for required commission metadata keys, tempo-band membership across many seeds, voice-count propagation, silence/restraint/harmony field propagation, sampler-density propagation, voice/groove/modal CSV serialization, the `mode_avoid_attention_pullers` string contract, deterministic application across non-zero seeds, input-dict immutability, JSON round-trip safety, and preservation of pre-existing commission keys; verify the entire `HOME_TONAL_MAP` (only `B` is home, `D` and `F#` are the unique distance-1 neighbors, every distance is a non-negative int); walk the documented `select_mode` priority matrix including the inclusive 0.6 STORM threshold, screen-active gating that requires `presence='present'`, equivalent evening/night routing, and a full presence/time/severity/screen sweep that always returns a known mode; sweep `next_tonal_choice` across many seeds for every mode confirming roots stay in `HOME_TONAL_MAP` and scales stay in `mode.preferred_modes`, determinism per (mode, seed), and that modulation-willingness correlates with venturing (SOLITARY <= COMPANION <= STORM); and run the end-to-end `select -> apply -> choose` pipeline across a presence/time/screen matrix with JSON-safe payloads. `tests/test_artist_identity_depth.py` pins the file's fractal depth at >= 2 (now `substantial (no tests)`, real_logic > trivial). Existing artist-identity assertions and the production `my-claw/tools/senseweave/artist_identity.py` source remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate remain green.
CHANGELOG.md:649:- Added depth-2 quota-aware agent selector end-to-end test coverage (frac-0057): `tests/test_agent_selector_quota.py` now ships a new `TestAgentSelectorEndToEnd` class that drives the existing public selector surface (`AgentSelector.select`, `select_pair`, `detect_category`, `record_outcome`, `status_summary`) through looped end-to-end methods. The new tests walk an alternation/rotation cycle across eight selects, round-trip selector state through `state_file` between two `AgentSelector` instances, sweep a category-detection table covering architecture/coding/review/research/testing/devops/netops/writing/routing/narrative_prose, run an Ollama health-recovery cycle (healthy → unhealthy → healthy) against the real `QuotaMonitor`, exercise pair selection across the default provider set, validate that `status_summary` lists every default agent and quota provider with mixed health statuses, confirm `disabled_agents` filtering is per-call rather than persistent across a sequence, sweep headrooms to flip the winner between providers, run `record_outcome` safely without an observatory across many calls, and verify that `select` raises `ValueError` when every available agent is disabled. `tests/test_agent_selector_quota_depth.py` pins the file's fractal depth at >= 2 (now `substantial (no tests)`, real_logic > trivial). Existing `TestAgentSelectorQuota` assertions and `agent_selector` / `quota_monitor` / `ollama_health` source modules remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate remain green.
CHANGELOG.md:685:- Added depth-2 trust manager planning (frac-0038): `promptclaw/coherence/trust.py` now exposes a frozen `TrustEventPlan` plus `trust_event_plans()` returning the canonical `hard_violation`, `soft_violation`, and `compliant_action` plans sourced from `TrustManager.HARD_PENALTY`, `SOFT_PENALTY`, and `COMPLIANT_REWARD`. `TrustManager.apply_event(agent, plan)` is the single mutation path — it validates the counter field against the canonical set, clamps the new score to `[0.0, 1.0]`, increments the named counter, touches the timestamp, and returns the new score. The legacy `apply_hard_violation`, `apply_soft_violation`, and `apply_compliant_action` methods now route through `apply_event` with the canonical plans so existing penalty/reward and clamp behavior is preserved. `apply_event_by_name`, `restricted_agents`, `summarize_agent`, and `fleet_summary` give operator surfaces a JSON-safe report with the configured constants, restriction threshold, alphabetically-ordered per-agent rows, and restricted-agent count. `tests/test_trust_depth.py` pins the canonical plan, apply-event routing, legacy-method delegation, JSON-safe sorted summary, unknown-counter rejection, and fractal depth >= 2; `tests/test_trust.py` remains the regression anchor for existing penalty/reward, clamping, restriction-threshold, and multi-agent isolation behavior.
CHANGELOG.md:699:- Added depth-2 synthesis architecture registry report helpers (frac-0031): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/synthesis_architecture_registry.py` now exposes frozen `ArchitectureProfile` and `ArchitectureRegistryReport` dataclasses plus pure helpers `affinity_band`, `control_span_band`, `fallback_chain`, `build_architecture_profile`, `build_architecture_registry_report`, and `summarize_architecture_registry_report` so planner/operator diagnostics can resolve the existing six-family synthesis strategy registry into a JSON-safe summary with ordered architecture IDs, phase winners, phase-ranked candidates, role-to-architecture mappings, fallback chains, macro-control defaults/span bands, high-affinity phase bands, missing coverage diagnostics, and per-architecture profiles. Existing registry entries and lookup behavior remain unchanged; `tests/test_synthesis_architecture_registry_depth.py` pins helper cutpoints, fallback-cycle handling, profile/report shape, JSON-safe summary stability, agreement with existing lookup helpers, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_synthesis_architecture_registry.py` and the startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:701:- Added depth-2 senseweave voice diagnostic helpers (frac-0030): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/synthesis/senseweave_voice.py` now exposes frozen `VoiceADSRSnapshot`, `VoiceNoteSnapshot`, and `VoicePlanReport` dataclasses plus pure helpers `voice_envelope_band`, `voice_amp_band`, `voice_register_band`, `voice_polyphony_band`, `voice_polyphony_pressure`, `is_voice_idle`, `preset_name_for_adsr`, `preset_envelope_band`, `voice_synth_for_timbre`, `summarize_active_notes`, `build_voice_adsr_snapshot`, `build_voice_note_snapshot`, `build_voice_plan_report`, `dominant_register_band`, `dominant_amp_band`, `dominant_synth`, and `summarize_voice_plan_report` so composer/operator diagnostics can resolve a live `SenseweaveVoice` (timbre, configured envelope, polyphony cap, active-note state, OSC synth) into a JSON-safe per-voice plan report with envelope band classification, amp/register/polyphony bands, preset-name reverse lookup, register/amp/synth count aggregates, and per-active-note snapshots without changing the OSC payload, polyphony cap, percussive-vs-sustained release, or convenience-helper behavior. `tests/test_senseweave_voice_depth.py` pins envelope/amp/register/polyphony/preset/timbre band cutpoints, frozen ADSR snapshot resolution, future-clock-clamped elapsed seconds, end-to-end voice plan report shape (preset_name, envelope, polyphony band, register/amp/synth counts, lowest/highest frequency, mean/total amp), JSON-safe summary stability, agreement with the helper surface for a deterministic active-note case, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_senseweave_voice.py`, `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence`, and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain regression anchors.
CHANGELOG.md:703:- Added depth-2 accompaniment decision report helpers (frac-0029): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/synthesis/accompaniment.py` now exposes frozen `AccompanimentPatternSnapshot` and `AccompanimentPlanReport` dataclasses plus pure helpers `accompaniment_density_band`, `accompaniment_pattern_name`, `accompaniment_energy_band`, `frequency_register_band`, `accompaniment_transition_mode`, `summarize_pattern_events`, `build_pattern_snapshot`, `build_accompaniment_plan_report`, and `summarize_accompaniment_plan_report` so composer/operator diagnostics can resolve the existing inverse-density accompaniment path into a JSON-safe decision summary. Existing `DensityTracker`, selection, six pattern helpers, pedal, breathing, transition, and tuple contracts are preserved; `tests/test_accompaniment_depth.py` pins band cutpoints, pattern snapshot aggregation, end-to-end density/breathing/pedal report output, JSON-safe summaries, agreement with the existing helpers, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_accompaniment.py` and the startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:705:- Added depth-2 SynthDef registry report helpers (frac-0028): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/synthdef_registry.py` now exposes frozen `VoiceShape` and `SynthDefRegistryReport` dataclasses plus pure helpers `register_band`, `fundamental_band`, `noise_band`, `rolloff_band`, `build_voice_shape`, `build_synthdef_registry_report`, and `summarize_synthdef_registry_report` so cast-planner / mix / operator-diagnostics callers can resolve the in-memory registry into operator-readable shape diagnostics — per-voice view (voice + synthdef name, synthesis method, timbral tags, safe roles, register min/max + rounded octave span + named register band, bandwidth, fundamental weight + named fundamental band, noise floor + named noise band, harmonic rolloff dB + named rolloff band, macro control count + ordered macro names, quarantine flag + reason + safe substitute, and resolved `runtime_voice_name`) and registry-level view (total/live/quarantined counts, canonical method ordering with full and live-only counts including zeros, ordered roles + role-to-live-voices map matching `voices_for_role`, ordered low/mid/high register-band counts, lowest/highest register voice names, ordered distinct quarantine reasons, ordered runtime-voice map for every quarantined voice, sorted tuple of canonical methods with zero entries, and ordered per-voice shapes) — and emit a JSON-safe summary mirroring those fields. Existing `REQUIRED_METHODS`, `SYNTHDEF_REGISTRY`, `RegisterRange`, `MacroControl`, `SpectralProfile`, `SynthDefEntry`, `get_entry`, `resolve_voice`, `entries_by_method`, `live_voices`, `quarantined_voices`, `voices_for_role`, and `covered_methods` semantics are preserved so downstream cast/composer/voice-alias callers and `tests/test_synthdef_registry.py` are unaffected; `tests/test_synthdef_registry_depth.py` pins band cutpoints, voice-shape resolution (live and quarantined `runtime_voice_name`), full-registry report shape (canonical method ordering, ordered roles excluding quarantined voices, register-band counts, lowest/highest registers, ordered quarantine reasons and runtime-voice map), JSON-safe summary stability, end-to-end agreement with `resolve_voice` / `live_voices` / `quarantined_voices` / `voices_for_role` / `covered_methods`, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_smoke_narrative_script.py` remains the regression anchor for the narrative HTTP `/healthz` + `/readyz` + bearer-token hardening surface.
CHANGELOG.md:769:- Added the CypherClaw narrative API regression suite plus a minimal auth gate (T-005@20260502T001347Z): `cypherclaw.narrative_api.create_app(...)` now accepts an optional `auth_token` keyword that, when set, requires every endpoint to carry a matching `X-Narrative-Auth` header (missing/wrong → 401); empty/unset preserves the existing auth-disabled behavior so T-010's env-var pull and startup warning land cleanly. `tests/test_narrative_api_memory.py` and `tests/test_narrative_api_events.py` now pin the four scenario floors (success path, auth failure when enabled, bad input validation, downstream-engine error handling) for `POST /memory/search`, `GET /events`, and `POST /events`, plus 503 fallback behavior when the deploy-side `cypherclaw.narrative.{memory,events}` package is absent and append-returns-None record synthesis. `pytest --cov=cypherclaw.narrative_api` reports 84% module coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:809:- Added `docs/cypherclaw-sampler-architecture.md` to fill the gap between the sampler PRD and the musicianship roadmap: it lists the landed sampler components (`sample_capture_daemon.py`, `sample_capture_verify.py`, `sampler_buffers.py`, `sampler_dispatch.py`, `synthesis/sampler_effects.scd`, `render/antipatterns.py`), traces the end-to-end signal flow from JACK input through capture, tagging, `index.sqlite`, dispatch, the `sw_sampler_fx` bus, and the master bus, names both live anti-pattern detectors (`sampler_dominating`, `sampler_silent_quintet_member`), enumerates integration seams (identity, cast planner, mix engine, composer, operator diagnostics), and explicitly flags `SampleLibrary`, `SampleSelector`, `sw_sampler.scd`, and quintet identity convergence as still pending; `tests/test_cypherclaw_sampler_architecture.py` pins the doc's required sections, the referenced file paths, and the live anti-pattern names so future renames or section drops force the doc to update with the code.
CHANGELOG.md:815:- Added audio-rendered novelty verification for SenseWeave fixtures: `render.audio_novelty` now writes deterministic 5-minute proxy WAVs, extracts librosa mel-feature self-similarity matrices plus Foote novelty curves, aligns symbolic CCH-034 novelty peak times to audio peaks within 500 ms, and fails flattened synthesis even when symbolic metrics remain healthy.
CHANGELOG.md:819:- Added executable production-course curriculum exercises: `ExerciseSpec` now carries a runnable `template` and explicit `expected_features` while preserving the legacy `expected` alias; generated exercise specs include both metadata forms; and the EMSD curriculum now has verifier-backed exercises for intervals/scales, chord voicings, progressions, rhythm/groove, counterpoint, synthesis architecture, mix/master, SenseWeave mapping, Theramini ensemble, genre strategy, and full-arc production.
CHANGELOG.md:820:- Added course-driven self-critique and revision targets: `self_critique.py` now maps production-course chapter concepts (mode_scale, harmonic_function, meter_groove, counterpoint_relation, synthesis_architecture, mix_role, spatial_intent, genre_strategy, transition_type, phase_profile) to concrete ear-engine metric thresholds via `COURSE_METRIC_MAP`; `thresholds_for_course()` merges per-section course metadata into quality thresholds (stricter wins); `critique_score_with_course()` returns a `CourseCritiqueReport` with `CourseFailure` attribution naming the specific course concept behind each metric violation; `revision_targets_from_failures()` maps failures to `RevisionTargets` specifying which musical dimensions (form, harmony, rhythm, register, mix, strategy) are open for bounded revision without changing piece identity; `revise_score()` accepts an optional `course` kwarg; `tracker_compiler.py` and `duet_composer.py` fallback paths now pass section production_course to `revise_score`.
CHANGELOG.md:921:- Widened tracker orchestration so CypherClaw can actually use the broader character-instrument registry: cast planning now keeps a support-role character in low-energy songs, tracker role hints recognize metal/grain/pad/tabla synths, and runtime voice routing preserves those explicit lane instruments instead of collapsing them to legacy fallbacks.
CHANGELOG.md:922:- Tuned tracker voice routing to be lane-aware again after the orchestration widening pass: ringing `metal`/`bell`/`pad` hints are normalized away from long quiet texture/counter lanes, and tracker runtime restores a pad safety fallback so subdued scenes do not sit on a constant unregulated tone.
CHANGELOG.md:933:- Added `LOCAL_ONLY` daemon enforcement so live routing collapses to `ollama`, bypasses cloud router CLIs, and coerces explicit cloud-agent steps back to the local agent.
CHANGELOG.md:937:- Added quota-aware graceful degradation for CypherClaw live command routing using `sdp-cli` provider headroom.
CHANGELOG.md:940:- Added provider status monitoring, runtime quota-error detection, Telegram `/quota` reporting, and routing fallback away from exhausted providers.
CHANGELOG.md:943:- Added quota-aware selector and daemon tests covering degraded-mode routing, retry fallback, and provider status transitions.
CHANGELOG.md:977:- Added 7 orchestrator hooks (pre/post routing, lead, verify, and finalize) for coherence checks.
